{"desi_lesson":{"title":"Lesson 1: Essential Survival Phrases in Telugu","target_language":"Telugu","theme":"Essential Survival Phrases","vocabulary":[{"english":"hello","target_language_script":"నమస్కారం","transliteration":"namaskaaram","pronunciation":"nuh-muh-skaa-rum"},{"english":"thank you","target_language_script":"ధన్యవాదాలు","transliteration":"dhanyavaadaalu","pronunciation":"dhan-ya-vaa-daalu"},{"english":"please","target_language_script":"దయచేసి","transliteration":"dayachesi","pronunciation":"day-a-che-see"},{"english":"excuse me","target_language_script":"క్షమించండి","transliteration":"kshamikandi","pronunciation":"ksha-min-chan-dee"},{"english":"yes","target_language_script":"అవును","transliteration":"avunu","pronunciation":"a-vu-nu"},{"english":"no","target_language_script":"లేదు","transliteration":"ledu","pronunciation":"lay-doo"},{"english":"I don't understand","target_language_script":"నేను అర్థం చేసుకోలేదు","transliteration":"nenu ardham chesukoledu","pronunciation":"nay-noo ar-tham che-su-ko-lay-doo"},{"english":"sorry","target_language_script":"క్షమించండి","transliteration":"kshaminchandi","pronunciation":"ksha-min-chan-dee"},{"english":"goodbye","target_language_script":"బాయ్","transliteration":"baay","pronunciation":"bay"},{"english":"help","target_language_script":"సహాయం","transliteration":"sahaayam","pronunciation":"suh-haa-yum"}],"example_sentences":[{"english":"Hello, how are you?","target_language_script":"ఎలా ఉన్నారు?","transliteration":"ela unnaaru?","pronunciation":"el-a un-naa-roo?"},{"english":"Thank you very much.","target_language_script":"చాలా ధన్యవాదాలు.","transliteration":"chaalaa dhanyavaadaalu.","pronunciation":"chaa-laa dhan-ya-vaa-daalu"},{"english":"Please help me.","target_language_script":"దయచేసి నాకు సహాయం చేయండి.","transliteration":"dayachesi naaku sahaayam cheyandi.","pronunciation":"day-a-che-see naa-koo suh-haa-yum che-yan-dee"},{"english":"Excuse me, where is the restroom?","target_language_script":"క్షమించండి, టాయిలె